---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { AUTHOR } from '../consts';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description={`About ${AUTHOR.name}`}>
  <h1>About</h1>

  <img
    src="/images/aslisho.jpg"
    alt={`Portrait of ${AUTHOR.name}`}
    width="160"
    height="160"
    class="portrait"
  />

  <p>
    I am <strong>{AUTHOR.name}</strong>, a Researcher at
    <a href="https://www.iis.ac.uk/">{AUTHOR.affiliation}</a> specialising in premodern history of West Asia and the Mediterranean world, while maintaining a lifelong passion for Persianate cultures across Central and West Asia.
  </p>

  <p>
    I have been trained in Arabic philology (Khorog State University, Tajikistan), then Islamic Studies and History (University of Oxford, 2012-14) and have a
    PhD in Middle Eastern Studies from the University of Cambridge (2015–2019),
    with a thesis entitled
    <em>
      Traditions of Learning in Fāṭimid Ifrīqiya (296–362/909–973): Networks,
      Practices, and Institutions
    </em>.
  </p>

  <p>
    I worked as a postdoctoral research fellow at the ERC-funded
    <a href="https://kitab-project.org/">KITAB Project</a> (AKU_ISMC, London), where my primary area of research was the Islamic West — the
    Maghrib, al-Andalus, and Sicily — alongside contributions to the
    <a href="https://openiti.org/">OpenITI corpus</a>. Otherwise, my research interests
    include the Fatimid empire and the wider Islamicate world, premodern
    education and knowledge practices, connectivity, book culture, and
    computational approaches to Arabic and Persian textual traditions. During my postdoctoral work with KITAB (2020-24) I acquired some knowledge of digital humanities and some of my experimentation with DH is featured here.
  </p>

  <p>
    I work primarily with English, Arabic, Persian, Turkish, Russian, Italian, and
    French.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Email: <a href={`mailto:${AUTHOR.email}`}>{AUTHOR.email}</a><br />
    X / Twitter: <a href="https://twitter.com/fatimid_studies">@fatimid_studies</a>
    (academic) · <a href="https://twitter.com/aslishahqurbani">@aslishahqurbani</a>
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Anything published on this site is experimental and mostly intended for
    sharing preliminary research ideas.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .portrait {
    float: right;
    border-radius: 10px;
    margin: 0 0 1rem 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .portrait {
      float: none;
      display: block;
      margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
